    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "In a lot of cases, changing a timeout from 1s to 5s in a test is totally fine, e.g. if we're waiting for an event, and in most cases it takes sub-second but in some cases takes longer. Changing the timeout then doesn't really affect the execution-time. \r\n\r\nHowever, we also have these cases, where adding N seconds makes the test take exactly N seconds longer. ",
